The paper discusses the optimization method for deep neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on the Hessian matrix, which is a tool used in optimization and numerical analysis, suggesting the paper could also belong to the category of numerical analysis (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the effect of noise on the Hessian matrix, which could fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The experiments conducted in the paper involve deep neural networks, which could also place the paper in the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or computer vision (cs.CV).
